  Translator: Burton Watson
By: Zhuangzi
Locus:
  Chapter: 17
  Paragraph: 35
Title: Autumn Floods
---
When Confucius was passing through Kuang, the men of Sung surrounded
him with several encirclements of troops, but he went right on playing
his lute and singing without a stop." Tzu Lu went in to see him and
said, "Master, how can you be so carefree?"
